    • regionMatches

      public static boolean regionMatches​(boolean ignoreCase, char[] thisVal, int thisOffset, char[] otherVal, int otherOffset, int len)
      Tests if two character array regions are equal.

      A subarray of thisVal argument is compared to a subarray of other argument. The result is true if these subarrays represent character sequences that are the same, ignoring case if and only if ignoreCase is true. The subarray of thisVal object to be compared begins at index thisOfffset and has length len. The subarray of otherVal to be compared begins at index otherOffset and has length len. The result is false if and only if at least one of the following is true:

      • thisOffset is negative.
      • otherOffset is negative.
      • thisOffset+len is greater than the length thisVal array.
      • otherOffset+len is greater than the length of the other argument.
      • ignoreCase is false and there is some nonnegative integer k less than len such that: 
         thisVal[thisOffset+k] != otherVal[otherOffset+k]
      • ignoreCase is true and there is some nonnegative integer k less than len such that: 
         Character.toLowerCase(thisVal[thisOffset+k]) !=
     Character.toLowerCase(otherVal[otherOffset+k])
        and: 
         Character.toUpperCase(thisVal[thisOffset+k]) !=
         Character.toUpperCase(otherVal(otherOffset+k))
      Parameters:
      ignoreCase - if true, ignore case when comparing characters.
      thisVal - an array of characters to compare to
      thisOffset - the starting offset of the subregion in thisVal argument
      otherVal - the other array of characters to be compare with.
      otherOffset - the starting offset of the subregion in the array character argument.
      len - the number of characters to compare.
      Returns:
      true if the specified subregion of this string matches the specified subregion of the string argument; false otherwise. Whether the matching is exact or case insensitive depends on the ignoreCase argument.
